The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Special envoy in PMO 

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, Aug. 22: S.K. Lambah, the convener of the National Security Advisory Board, was today appointed special envoy in the Prime Ministers Office in the rank of secretary.

 Lambah has headed the Indian mission in Islamabad and Moscow and served as special envoy to Afghanistan.

 M.K. Rasgotra, the former foreign secretary, will take over as the new National Security Advisory Board convener for a two-year term. An official release said four new members were added to the board ? K.S. Rao, former chief secretary of Sikkim, V.K. Jain, a former special secretary in the home ministry, N.S. Sisodia, former secretary in the finance ministry, and Roddan Narasimha, chairman (engineering mechanics unit) in the Jawaharlal Nehru Centre for Advanced Scientific Research.




